'''Kelewele''' yɛ [[Ghana|Gana aduane a agye din]] na yɛ de spices aka borɔdeɛ ho akye. Wɔ   [[English|Brofo]] mu no, wɔ frɛ no '''hot plantain crisps'''. Wɔ  [[Nkran|Accra]], wɔ tɔn kelewele anadwo wɔ kwan nkyɛn na etɔ da nso a wɔ tɔn no ewia bere. Wɔ betumi de edi  adua forɔeɛ, nkate, anaa wɔ bedi no saa sɛ dessert.  Wɔ betumi edi kelewele  anadwo .

Aduane yi fi [[Ghana|Gana]], kelewele agye din wɔ [[United States|Amerika]]  a ɛwɛ nhoma a yɛ hwɛ so de nua aduane mu (recipezaar, 2009)

=== Ɔkwan a wɔ fa so yɛ ===
Wɔ wane borɔdeɛ no ho na watwetwa no nketewa. Akakaduro, meko a ɛsheshe, ne nkyen na ɛyɛ neɛma a wɔ taa de ka ho yɛ kekewele kelewele. Wɔ betumi de Gyeene, nketenkete, pɛprɛ, nutmeg, cinnamon,ne  meko sam,  aka ho. Sɛ wɔ yɛ atɔn a nhyehyɛyɛ da ha ɛwɔ sɛ wo hyɛ so yɛ na ne dɛ no ansesa. Nhwɛsoɔ ne sɛ , ɛwɔ sɛ  angwa no yɛ she paa na borɔde no nso nyɛ merɛ beberee enyɛ saa a borɔde no bɛ num angwa nol.  Wɔ kye borɔde no kosi sɛ asikyire na ɛwɔ mu no bɛ na ne na borɔde no ho bɛ yɛ asaase ahosuo no.

